import { 
    Navbar, 
    Nav, 
    NavDropdown, 
    Container,
    Offcanvas,
    Button } from 'react-bootstrap'

import { useState } from 'react';
import '../styles/Header.css'

export default function Header({ children }){

    const [show, setShow] = useState(false);

    const handleClose = () => setShow(false);
    const toggleShow = () => setShow((s) => !s);

    return (
        <>
            <Navbar position="sticky" collapseOnSelect expand="lg" bg="light" variant="light" className="p-3">
                <Container>
                    <Navbar.Toggle aria-controls="aria-navbar-nav" />
                    <Navbar.Collapse id="aria-navbar-nav">
                        <Nav  className="my-2">
                            <Nav.Link href="#features">HOME</Nav.Link>
                            <Nav.Link href="#pricing">SHOP</Nav.Link>
                            <Nav.Link href="#pricing">BLOG</Nav.Link>
                            <Nav.Link href="#pricing">CONTACT</Nav.Link>
                        </Nav>
                    </Navbar.Collapse>
                    
                    <Nav className="brand-nav me-auto">
                        <Navbar.Brand href="#home">
                            CORNELIA
                        </Navbar.Brand>
                    </Nav>

                    <Nav>
                            <Nav.Link href="#features">LOGIN</Nav.Link>
                            <Nav.Link href="#pricing">CART(0)</Nav.Link>
                            <Nav.Link className="bi bi-search"></Nav.Link>
                    </Nav>

                    {
                        /*
                            <Nav className="right-nav">
                        <Nav.Link className="bi bi-search" href="#memes"></Nav.Link>
                        <Nav.Link onClick={toggleShow} className="bi bi-cart4"/>

                        <Offcanvas show={show} onHide={handleClose} scroll={true} backdrop={false}>
                            <Offcanvas.Header  closeButton="true" closeLabel="canvas-close">
                                <Offcanvas.Title>
                                    Offcanvas
                                </Offcanvas.Title>
                            </Offcanvas.Header>

                            <Offcanvas.Body>
                                Some text as placeholder. In real life you can have the elements you
                                have chosen. Like, text, images, lists, etc.
                            </Offcanvas.Body>
                        </Offcanvas>

                        <Nav.Link className="bi bi-person" href="#deets"></Nav.Link>
                    </Nav>
                        */
                    }
                </Container>
                
            </Navbar>
            
        </>
    )
}
